examples.en: They live in this block.
Please don't block the doorway.
He lives in the next block.
The garage was made of concrete blocks.
examples.ru: Гараж был построен из бетонных блоков.

examples.en: They went around the block.
The sink's blocked up.
Hats cleaned and blocked.
examples.ru: Шляпы вычищены и надеты на болванку.

examples.en: You'd better block up that hole in the wall; it's letting the cold in.
examples.ru: Заделай-ка дыру в стене, оттуда дует.

examples.en: She lived on our block.
A fallen tree is blocking the road.
Her arteries are blocked.
Let's walk round the block.
The office block looks as if it's just been chucked up.
Can you move? You're blocking my light.
examples.ru: Можешь отойти? Ты мне свет загораживаешь.

examples.en: His vote blocked the treaty.
An accident was blocking traffic.
His brother blocked him at every turn.
examples.ru: Брат мешал ему на каждом шагу.

examples.en: The building occupies an entire city block.
The Senate blocked publication of the report.
Please don't block the door.
The Liberals vote as a block
The church is down the block.
My plans hit a stumbling block.
examples.ru: Мои планы наткнулись на серьёзное препятствие /камень преткновения/.

examples.en: We took a walk around the block.
Snowdrifts blocked our progress.
They live just up the block from us.
examples.ru: Они живут всего в квартале от нас.

examples.en: Our hotel is a block from the ocean.
examples.ru: Наша гостиница находится в одном квартале от океана.

examples.en: The clouds have blocked out the sun.
There's an accident blocking the road.
We grew up down the block from each other.
examples.ru: Мы выросли в квартале друг от друга.
